137static void cancelAll(const ResourceLoaderMap& loaders)
138{
139 for (auto& loader : copyToVector(loaders.values()))
140 loader->cancel();
141}
142
143static void setAllDefersLoading(const ResourceLoaderMap& loaders, bool defers)
144{
145 for (auto& loader : copyToVector(loaders.values()))
146 loader->setDefersLoading(defers);
147}

149static HashMap<DocumentIdentifier, DocumentLoader*>& temporaryIdentifierToLoaderMap()
150{
151 static NeverDestroyed<HashMap<DocumentIdentifier, DocumentLoader*>> map;
152 return map.get();
153}
154
155DocumentLoader* DocumentLoader::fromTemporaryDocumentIdentifier(DocumentIdentifier identifier)
156{
157 return temporaryIdentifierToLoaderMap().get(identifier);
158}

162DocumentLoader::DocumentLoader(const ResourceRequest& request, const SubstituteData& substituteData)
163 : FrameDestructionObserver(nullptr)
164 , m_cachedResourceLoader(CachedResourceLoader::create(this))
165 , m_originalRequest(request)
166 , m_substituteData(substituteData)
167 , m_originalRequestCopy(request)
168 , m_request(request)
169 , m_originalSubstituteDataWasValid(substituteData.isValid())
170 , m_substituteResourceDeliveryTimer(*this, &DocumentLoader::substituteResourceDeliveryTimerFired)
171 , m_applicationCacheHost(makeUnique<ApplicationCacheHost>(*this))
172{
173}
174
175FrameLoader* DocumentLoader::frameLoader() const
176{
177 if (!m_frame)
178 return nullptr;
179 return &m_frame->loader();
180}
181
182SubresourceLoader* DocumentLoader::mainResourceLoader() const
183{
184 if (!m_mainResource)
185 return nullptr;
186 return m_mainResource->loader();
187}
188
189DocumentLoader::~DocumentLoader()
190{
191 ASSERT(!m_frame || !isLoading() || frameLoader()->activeDocumentLoader() != this);
192 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(!m_waitingForContentPolicy, "The content policy callback should never outlive its DocumentLoader.");
193 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(!m_waitingForNavigationPolicy, "The navigation policy callback should never outlive its DocumentLoader.");
194
195 m_cachedResourceLoader->clearDocumentLoader();
196 clearMainResource();
197
198#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
199 if (m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient) {
200 ASSERT(temporaryIdentifierToLoaderMap().contains(*m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient));
201 temporaryIdentifierToLoaderMap().remove(*m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient);
202 }
203#endif
204}
205
206RefPtr<SharedBuffer> DocumentLoader::mainResourceData() const
207{
208 if (m_substituteData.isValid())
209 return m_substituteData.content()->copy();
210 if (m_mainResource)
211 return m_mainResource->resourceBuffer();
212 return nullptr;
213}

215Document* DocumentLoader::document() const
216{
217 if (m_frame && m_frame->loader().documentLoader() == this)
218 return m_frame->document();
219 return nullptr;
220}

222void DocumentLoader::replaceRequestURLForSameDocumentNavigation(const URL& url)
223{
224 m_originalRequestCopy.setURL(url);
225 m_request.setURL(url);
226}
227
228void DocumentLoader::setRequest(const ResourceRequest& req)
229{
230 // Replacing an unreachable URL with alternate content looks like a server-side
231 // redirect at this point, but we can replace a committed dataSource.
232 bool handlingUnreachableURL = false;
233
234 handlingUnreachableURL = m_substituteData.isValid() && !m_substituteData.failingURL().isEmpty();
235
236 bool shouldNotifyAboutProvisionalURLChange = false;
237 if (handlingUnreachableURL)
238 m_committed = false;
239 else if (isLoadingMainResource() && req.url() != m_request.url())
240 shouldNotifyAboutProvisionalURLChange = true;
241
242 // We should never be getting a redirect callback after the data
243 // source is committed, except in the unreachable URL case. It
244 // would be a WebFoundation bug if it sent a redirect callback after commit.
245 ASSERT(!m_committed);
246
247 m_request = req;
248 if (shouldNotifyAboutProvisionalURLChange) {
249 // Logging for <rdar://problem/54830233>.
250 if (!frameLoader()->provisionalDocumentLoader())
251 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("DocumentLoader::setRequest: With no provisional document loader");
252 frameLoader()->client().dispatchDidChangeProvisionalURL();
253 }
254}
255
256void DocumentLoader::setMainDocumentError(const ResourceError& error)
257{
258 if (!error.isNull())
259 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("setMainDocumentError: (type=%d, code=%d)", static_cast<int>(error.type()), error.errorCode());
260
261 m_mainDocumentError = error;
262 frameLoader()->client().setMainDocumentError(this, error);
263}
264
265void DocumentLoader::mainReceivedError(const ResourceError& error)
266{
267 ASSERT(!error.isNull());
268
269 if (!frameLoader())
270 return;
271
272 if (!error.isNull())
273 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("mainReceivedError: (type=%d, code=%d)", static_cast<int>(error.type()), error.errorCode());
274
275 if (m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader) {
276 ASSERT(!mainResourceLoader());
277 frameLoader()->client().dispatchDidFailLoading(this, m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, error);
278 }
279
280 // There is a bug in CFNetwork where callbacks can be dispatched even when loads are deferred.
281 // See <rdar://problem/6304600> for more details.
282#if !USE(CF)
283 ASSERT(!mainResourceLoader() || !mainResourceLoader()->defersLoading());
284#endif
285
286 m_applicationCacheHost->failedLoadingMainResource();
287
288 setMainDocumentError(error);
289 clearMainResourceLoader();
290 frameLoader()->receivedMainResourceError(error);
291}
292
293void DocumentLoader::frameDestroyed()
294{
295 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("DocumentLoader::frameDestroyed: m_frame=%p", m_frame.get());
296 FrameDestructionObserver::frameDestroyed();
297}
298
299// Cancels the data source's pending loads. Conceptually, a data source only loads
300// one document at a time, but one document may have many related resources.
301// stopLoading will stop all loads initiated by the data source,
302// but not loads initiated by child frames' data sources -- that's the WebFrame's job.
303void DocumentLoader::stopLoading()
304{
305 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("DocumentLoader::stopLoading: m_frame=%p", m_frame.get());
306
307 ASSERT(m_frame);
308 if (!m_frame)
309 return;
310
311 RefPtr<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame.get());
312 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
313
314 // In some rare cases, calling FrameLoader::stopLoading could cause isLoading() to return false.
315 // (This can happen when there's a single XMLHttpRequest currently loading and stopLoading causes it
316 // to stop loading. Because of this, we need to save it so we don't return early.
317 bool loading = isLoading();
318
319 if (m_committed) {
320 // Attempt to stop the frame if the document loader is loading, or if it is done loading but
321 // still parsing. Failure to do so can cause a world leak.
322 Document* doc = m_frame->document();
323
324 if (loading || doc->parsing())
325 m_frame->loader().stopLoading(UnloadEventPolicy::None);
326 }
327
328 for (auto& callback : m_iconLoaders.values())
329 callback(nullptr);
330 m_iconLoaders.clear();
331 m_iconsPendingLoadDecision.clear();
332
333#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
334 for (auto callbackIdentifier : m_applicationManifestLoaders.values())
335 notifyFinishedLoadingApplicationManifest(callbackIdentifier, std::nullopt);
336 m_applicationManifestLoaders.clear();
337#endif
338
339 // Always cancel multipart loaders
340 cancelAll(m_multipartSubresourceLoaders);
341
342 if (auto* document = this->document())
343 document->suspendFontLoading();
344
345 // Appcache uses ResourceHandle directly, DocumentLoader doesn't count these loads.
346 m_applicationCacheHost->stopLoadingInFrame(*m_frame);
347
348#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
349 clearArchiveResources();
350#endif
351
352 if (!loading) {
353 // If something above restarted loading we might run into mysterious crashes like
354 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=62764 and <rdar://problem/9328684>
355 ASSERT(!isLoading());
356 return;
357 }
358
359 // We might run in to infinite recursion if we're stopping loading as the result of
360 // detaching from the frame, so break out of that recursion here.
361 // See <rdar://problem/9673866> for more details.
362 if (m_isStopping)
363 return;
364
365 m_isStopping = true;
366
367 // The frame may have been detached from this document by the onunload handler
368 if (auto* frameLoader = DocumentLoader::frameLoader()) {
369 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("stopLoading: canceling load");
370 if (isLoadingMainResource()) {
371 // Stop the main resource loader and let it send the cancelled message.
372 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader->cancelledError(m_request));
373 } else if (!m_subresourceLoaders.isEmpty() || !m_plugInStreamLoaders.isEmpty()) {
374 // The main resource loader already finished loading. Set the cancelled error on the
375 // document and let the subresourceLoaders and pluginLoaders send individual cancelled messages below.
376 setMainDocumentError(frameLoader->cancelledError(m_request));
377 } else {
378 // If there are no resource loaders, we need to manufacture a cancelled message.
379 // (A back/forward navigation has no resource loaders because its resources are cached.)
380 mainReceivedError(frameLoader->cancelledError(m_request));
381 }
382 }
383
384 // We always need to explicitly cancel the Document's parser when stopping the load.
385 // Otherwise cancelling the parser while starting the next page load might result
386 // in unexpected side effects such as erroneous event dispatch. ( http://webkit.org/b/117112 )
387 if (Document* document = this->document())
388 document->cancelParsing();
389
390 stopLoadingSubresources();
391 stopLoadingPlugIns();
392
393 m_isStopping = false;
394}
395
396void DocumentLoader::commitIfReady()
397{
398 if (!m_committed) {
399 m_committed = true;
400 frameLoader()->commitProvisionalLoad();
401 }
402}
403
404bool DocumentLoader::isLoading() const
405{
406 // if (document() && document()->hasActiveParser())
407 // return true;
408 // FIXME: The above code should be enabled, but it seems to cause
409 // http/tests/security/feed-urls-from-remote.html to timeout on Mac WK1
410 // see http://webkit.org/b/110554 and http://webkit.org/b/110401
411
412 return isLoadingMainResource() || !m_subresourceLoaders.isEmpty() || !m_plugInStreamLoaders.isEmpty();
413}
414
415void DocumentLoader::notifyFinished(CachedResource& resource, const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
416{
417 ASSERT(isMainThread());
418#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
419 if (m_contentFilter && !m_contentFilter->continueAfterNotifyFinished(resource))
420 return;
421#endif
422
423 if (auto document = makeRefPtr(this->document())) {
424 if (auto domWindow = makeRefPtr(document->domWindow())) {
425 if (document->settings().performanceNavigationTimingAPIEnabled())
426 domWindow->performance().addNavigationTiming(*this, *document, resource, timing(), metrics);
427 }
428 }
429
430 ASSERT_UNUSED(resource, m_mainResource == &resource);
431 ASSERT(m_mainResource);
432 if (!m_mainResource->errorOccurred() && !m_mainResource->wasCanceled()) {
433 finishedLoading();
434 return;
435 }
436
437 if (m_request.cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataDontLoad && !m_mainResource->wasCanceled()) {
438 frameLoader()->retryAfterFailedCacheOnlyMainResourceLoad();
439 return;
440 }
441
442 if (!m_mainResource->resourceError().isNull())
443 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("notifyFinished: canceling load (type=%d, code=%d)", static_cast<int>(m_mainResource->resourceError().type()), m_mainResource->resourceError().errorCode());
444
445 mainReceivedError(m_mainResource->resourceError());
446}
447
448void DocumentLoader::finishedLoading()
449{
450 // There is a bug in CFNetwork where callbacks can be dispatched even when loads are deferred.
451 // See <rdar://problem/6304600> for more details.
452#if !USE(CF)
453 ASSERT(!m_frame->page()->defersLoading() || frameLoader()->stateMachine().creatingInitialEmptyDocument() || InspectorInstrumentation::isDebuggerPaused(m_frame.get()));
454#endif
455
456 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
457
458 if (m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader) {
459 // A didFinishLoading delegate might try to cancel the load (despite it
460 // being finished). Clear m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader
461 // before calling dispatchDidFinishLoading so that we don't later try to
462 // cancel the already-finished substitute load.
463 NetworkLoadMetrics emptyMetrics;
464 unsigned long identifier = m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader;
465 m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader = 0;
466 frameLoader()->notifier().dispatchDidFinishLoading(this, identifier, emptyMetrics, nullptr);
467 }
468
469 maybeFinishLoadingMultipartContent();
470
471 timing().markEndTime();
472
473 commitIfReady();
474 if (!frameLoader())
475 return;
476
477 if (!maybeCreateArchive()) {
478 // If this is an empty document, it will not have actually been created yet. Commit dummy data so that
479 // DocumentWriter::begin() gets called and creates the Document.
480 if (!m_gotFirstByte)
481 commitData(0, 0);
482
483 if (!frameLoader())
484 return;
485 frameLoader()->client().finishedLoading(this);
486 }
487
488 m_writer.end();
489 if (!m_mainDocumentError.isNull())
490 return;
491 clearMainResourceLoader();
492 if (!frameLoader())
493 return;
494 if (!frameLoader()->stateMachine().creatingInitialEmptyDocument())
495 frameLoader()->checkLoadComplete();
496
497 // If the document specified an application cache manifest, it violates the author's intent if we store it in the memory cache
498 // and deny the appcache the chance to intercept it in the future, so remove from the memory cache.
499 if (m_frame) {
500 if (m_mainResource && m_frame->document()->hasManifest())
501 MemoryCache::singleton().remove(*m_mainResource);
502 }
503 m_applicationCacheHost->finishedLoadingMainResource();
504}
505
506static bool isRedirectToGetAfterPost(const ResourceRequest& oldRequest, const ResourceRequest& newRequest)
507{
508 return oldRequest.httpMethod() == "POST" && newRequest.httpMethod() == "GET";
509}
510
511bool DocumentLoader::isPostOrRedirectAfterPost(const ResourceRequest& newRequest, const ResourceResponse& redirectResponse)
512{
513 if (newRequest.httpMethod() == "POST")
514 return true;
515
516 int status = redirectResponse.httpStatusCode();
517 if (((status >= 301 && status <= 303) || status == 307)
518 && m_originalRequest.httpMethod() == "POST")
519 return true;
520
521 return false;
522}
523
524void DocumentLoader::handleSubstituteDataLoadNow()
525{
526 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
527
528 ResourceResponse response = m_substituteData.response();
529 if (response.url().isEmpty())
530 response = ResourceResponse(m_request.url(), m_substituteData.mimeType(), m_substituteData.content()->size(), m_substituteData.textEncoding());
531
532#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
533 if (auto* page = m_frame ? m_frame->page() : nullptr) {
534 // We intentionally do nothing with the results of this call.
535 // We want the CSS to be loaded for us, but we ignore any attempt to block or upgrade the connection since there is no connection.
536 page->userContentProvider().processContentRuleListsForLoad(*page, response.url(), ContentExtensions::ResourceType::Document, *this);
537 }
538#endif
539
540 responseReceived(response, nullptr);
541}

543#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
544bool DocumentLoader::setControllingServiceWorkerRegistration(ServiceWorkerRegistrationData&& data)
545{
546 if (!m_loadingMainResource)
547 return false;
548
549 ASSERT(!m_gotFirstByte);
550 m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData = WTFMove(data);
551 return true;
552}
553
554void DocumentLoader::matchRegistration(const URL& url, SWClientConnection::RegistrationCallback&& callback)
555{
556 auto shouldTryLoadingThroughServiceWorker = !frameLoader()->isReloadingFromOrigin() && m_frame->page() && RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled() && url.protocolIsInHTTPFamily();
557 if (!shouldTryLoadingThroughServiceWorker) {
558 callback(std::nullopt);
559 return;
560 }
561
562 auto origin = (!m_frame->isMainFrame() && m_frame->document()) ? m_frame->document()->topOrigin().data() : SecurityOriginData::fromURL(url);
563 if (!ServiceWorkerProvider::singleton().serviceWorkerConnection().mayHaveServiceWorkerRegisteredForOrigin(origin)) {
564 callback(std::nullopt);
565 return;
566 }
567
568 auto& connection = ServiceWorkerProvider::singleton().serviceWorkerConnection();
569 connection.matchRegistration(WTFMove(origin), url, WTFMove(callback));
570}
571
572static inline bool areRegistrationsEqual(const std::optional<ServiceWorkerRegistrationData>& a, const std::optional<ServiceWorkerRegistrationData>& b)
573{
574 if (!a)
575 return !b;
576 if (!b)
577 return false;
578 return a->identifier == b->identifier;
579}
580#endif
581
582void DocumentLoader::redirectReceived(CachedResource& resource, ResourceRequest&& request, const ResourceResponse& redirectResponse, CompletionHandler<void(ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
583{
584 ASSERT_UNUSED(resource, &resource == m_mainResource);
585#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
586 if (m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData) {
587 m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData = { };
588 unregisterTemporaryServiceWorkerClient();
589 }
590 willSendRequest(WTFMove(request), redirectResponse, [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), protectedThis = makeRef(*this), this] (auto&& request) mutable {
591 ASSERT(!m_substituteData.isValid());
592 if (request.isNull() || !m_mainDocumentError.isNull() || !m_frame) {
593 completionHandler({ });
594 return;
595 }
596
597 if (m_applicationCacheHost->canLoadMainResource(request)) {
598 auto url = request.url();
599 // Let's check service worker registration to see whether loading from network or not.
600 this->matchRegistration(url, [request = WTFMove(request), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), this](auto&& registrationData) mutable {
601 if (!m_mainDocumentError.isNull() || !m_frame) {
602 completionHandler({ });
603 return;
604 }
605 if (!registrationData && this->tryLoadingRedirectRequestFromApplicationCache(request)) {
606 completionHandler({ });
607 return;
608 }
609 completionHandler(WTFMove(request));
610 });
611 return;
612 }
613 completionHandler(WTFMove(request));
614 });
615#else
616 willSendRequest(WTFMove(request), redirectResponse, WTFMove(completionHandler));
617#endif
618}
619
620void DocumentLoader::willSendRequest(ResourceRequest&& newRequest, const ResourceResponse& redirectResponse, CompletionHandler<void(ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
621{
622 // Note that there are no asserts here as there are for the other callbacks. This is due to the
623 // fact that this "callback" is sent when starting every load, and the state of callback
624 // deferrals plays less of a part in this function in preventing the bad behavior deferring
625 // callbacks is meant to prevent.
626 ASSERT(!newRequest.isNull());
627
628 // Logging for <rdar://problem/54830233>.
629 if (!frameLoader() || !frameLoader()->provisionalDocumentLoader())
630 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRequest: With no provisional document loader");
631
632 bool didReceiveRedirectResponse = !redirectResponse.isNull();
633 if (!frameLoader()->checkIfFormActionAllowedByCSP(newRequest.url(), didReceiveRedirectResponse)) {
634 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRequest: canceling - form action not allowed by CSP");
635 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->cancelledError(newRequest));
636 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
637 }
638
639 ASSERT(timing().startTime());
640 if (didReceiveRedirectResponse) {
641 // If the redirecting url is not allowed to display content from the target origin,
642 // then block the redirect.
643 Ref<SecurityOrigin> redirectingOrigin(SecurityOrigin::create(redirectResponse.url()));
644 if (!redirectingOrigin.get().canDisplay(newRequest.url())) {
645 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRequest: canceling - redirecting URL not allowed to display content from target");
646 FrameLoader::reportLocalLoadFailed(m_frame.get(), newRequest.url().string());
647 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->cancelledError(newRequest));
648 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
649 }
650 if (!portAllowed(newRequest.url())) {
651 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRequest: canceling - redirecting to a URL with a blocked port");
652 if (m_frame)
653 FrameLoader::reportBlockedLoadFailed(*m_frame, newRequest.url());
654 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->blockedError(newRequest));
655 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
656 }
657 }
658
659 ASSERT(m_frame);
660
661 Frame& topFrame = m_frame->tree().top();
662
663 ASSERT(m_frame->document());
664 ASSERT(topFrame.document());
665
666 // Update cookie policy base URL as URL changes, except for subframes, which use the
667 // URL of the main frame which doesn't change when we redirect.
668 if (m_frame->isMainFrame())
669 newRequest.setFirstPartyForCookies(newRequest.url());
670
671 FrameLoader::addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(newRequest, m_frame->document());
672
673 if (!didReceiveRedirectResponse)
674 frameLoader()->client().dispatchWillChangeDocument(m_frame->document()->url(), newRequest.url());
675
676 // If we're fielding a redirect in response to a POST, force a load from origin, since
677 // this is a common site technique to return to a page viewing some data that the POST
678 // just modified.
679 // Also, POST requests always load from origin, but this does not affect subresources.
680 if (newRequest.cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy && isPostOrRedirectAfterPost(newRequest, redirectResponse))
681 newRequest.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData);
682
683 if (isRedirectToGetAfterPost(m_request, newRequest))
684 newRequest.clearHTTPOrigin();
685
686 if (&topFrame != m_frame) {
687 if (!MixedContentChecker::canDisplayInsecureContent(*m_frame, m_frame->document()->securityOrigin(), MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active, newRequest.url(), MixedContentChecker::AlwaysDisplayInNonStrictMode::Yes)) {
688 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->cancelledError(newRequest));
689 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
690 }
691 if (!MixedContentChecker::canDisplayInsecureContent(*m_frame, topFrame.document()->securityOrigin(), MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active, newRequest.url())) {
692 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->cancelledError(newRequest));
693 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
694 }
695 }
696
697 if (!newRequest.url().host().isEmpty() && SecurityOrigin::shouldIgnoreHost(newRequest.url())) {
698 auto url = newRequest.url();
699 url.setHostAndPort({ });
700 newRequest.setURL(WTFMove(url));
701 }
702
703#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
704 if (m_contentFilter && !m_contentFilter->continueAfterWillSendRequest(newRequest, redirectResponse))
705 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
706#endif
707
708 setRequest(newRequest);
709
710 if (!didReceiveRedirectResponse)
711 return completionHandler(WTFMove(newRequest));
712
713 auto navigationPolicyCompletionHandler = [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), protectedFrame = makeRef(*m_frame), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (ResourceRequest&& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&&, NavigationPolicyDecision navigationPolicyDecision) mutable {
714 m_waitingForNavigationPolicy = false;
715 switch (navigationPolicyDecision) {
716 case NavigationPolicyDecision::IgnoreLoad:
717 case NavigationPolicyDecision::StopAllLoads:
718 stopLoadingForPolicyChange();
719 break;
720 case NavigationPolicyDecision::ContinueLoad:
721 break;
722 }
723
724 completionHandler(WTFMove(request));
725 };
726
727 ASSERT(!m_waitingForNavigationPolicy);
728 m_waitingForNavigationPolicy = true;
729
730 // FIXME: Add a load type check.
731 auto& policyChecker = frameLoader()->policyChecker();
732 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isBackForwardLoadType(policyChecker.loadType()) || frameLoader()->history().provisionalItem());
733 policyChecker.checkNavigationPolicy(WTFMove(newRequest), redirectResponse, WTFMove(navigationPolicyCompletionHandler));
734}
735
736bool DocumentLoader::tryLoadingRequestFromApplicationCache()
737{
738 m_applicationCacheHost->maybeLoadMainResource(m_request, m_substituteData);
739 return tryLoadingSubstituteData();
740}
741
742bool DocumentLoader::tryLoadingSubstituteData()
743{
744 if (!m_substituteData.isValid() || !m_frame->page())
745 return false;
746
747 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource: Returning substitute data");
748 m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader = m_frame->page()->progress().createUniqueIdentifier();
749 frameLoader()->notifier().assignIdentifierToInitialRequest(m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, this, m_request);
750 frameLoader()->notifier().dispatchWillSendRequest(this, m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, m_request, ResourceResponse(), nullptr);
751
752 if (!m_deferMainResourceDataLoad || frameLoader()->loadsSynchronously())
753 handleSubstituteDataLoadNow();
754 else {
755 auto loadData = [this, weakDataLoadToken = makeWeakPtr(m_dataLoadToken)] {
756 if (!weakDataLoadToken)
757 return;
758 m_dataLoadToken.clear();
759 handleSubstituteDataLoadNow();
760 };
761
762#if USE(COCOA_EVENT_LOOP)
763 RunLoop::dispatch(*m_frame->page()->scheduledRunLoopPairs(), WTFMove(loadData));
764#else
765 RunLoop::current().dispatch(WTFMove(loadData));
766#endif
767 }
768
769 return true;
770}
771
772bool DocumentLoader::tryLoadingRedirectRequestFromApplicationCache(const ResourceRequest& request)
773{
774 m_applicationCacheHost->maybeLoadMainResourceForRedirect(request, m_substituteData);
775 if (!m_substituteData.isValid())
776 return false;
777
778 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_mainResource);
779 auto* loader = m_mainResource->loader();
780 m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader = loader ? loader->identifier() : m_mainResource->identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader();
781
782 // We need to remove our reference to the CachedResource in favor of a SubstituteData load, which can triger the cancellation of the underyling ResourceLoader.
783 // If the ResourceLoader is indeed cancelled, it would normally send resource load callbacks.
784 // Therefore, sever our relationship with the network load but prevent the ResourceLoader from sending ResourceLoadNotifier callbacks.
785
786 auto resourceLoader = makeRefPtr(mainResourceLoader());
787 if (resourceLoader) {
788 ASSERT(resourceLoader->shouldSendResourceLoadCallbacks());
789 resourceLoader->setSendCallbackPolicy(SendCallbackPolicy::DoNotSendCallbacks);
790 }
791
792 clearMainResource();
793
794 if (resourceLoader)
795 resourceLoader->setSendCallbackPolicy(SendCallbackPolicy::SendCallbacks);
796
797 handleSubstituteDataLoadNow();
798 return true;
799}
800
801void DocumentLoader::stopLoadingAfterXFrameOptionsOrContentSecurityPolicyDenied(unsigned long identifier, const ResourceResponse& response)
802{
803 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis { *this };
804 InspectorInstrumentation::continueAfterXFrameOptionsDenied(*m_frame, identifier, *this, response);
805 m_frame->document()->enforceSandboxFlags(SandboxOrigin);
806 if (HTMLFrameOwnerElement* ownerElement = m_frame->ownerElement())
807 ownerElement->dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().loadEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
808
809 // The load event might have detached this frame. In that case, the load will already have been cancelled during detach.
810 if (FrameLoader* frameLoader = this->frameLoader())
811 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader->cancelledError(m_request));
812}

814#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
815static URL microsoftTeamsRedirectURL()
816{
817 return URL(URL(), "https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/microsoft-teams/");
818}
819#endif
820
821void DocumentLoader::responseReceived(CachedResource& resource, const ResourceResponse& response, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
822{
823 ASSERT_UNUSED(resource, m_mainResource == &resource);
824
825#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
826 // FIXME(218779): Remove this quirk once microsoft.com completes their login flow redesign.
827 if (m_frame && m_frame->document()) {
828 auto& document = *m_frame->document();
829 if (Quirks::isMicrosoftTeamsRedirectURL(response.url())) {
830 auto firstPartyDomain = RegistrableDomain(response.url());
831 if (auto loginDomains = NetworkStorageSession::subResourceDomainsInNeedOfStorageAccessForFirstParty(firstPartyDomain)) {
832 if (!Quirks::hasStorageAccessForAllLoginDomains(*loginDomains, firstPartyDomain)) {
833 m_frame->navigationScheduler().scheduleRedirect(document, 0, microsoftTeamsRedirectURL());
834 return;
835 }
836 }
837 }
838 }
839#endif
840
841#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
842 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled() && response.source() == ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCache) {
843 matchRegistration(response.url(), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), response, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](auto&& registrationData) mutable {
844 if (!m_mainDocumentError.isNull() || !m_frame) {
845 completionHandler();
846 return;
847 }
848 m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData = WTFMove(registrationData);
849 responseReceived(response, WTFMove(completionHandler));
850 });
851 return;
852 }
853#endif
854 responseReceived(response, WTFMove(completionHandler));
855}
856
857void DocumentLoader::responseReceived(const ResourceResponse& response, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
858{
859 ASSERT(response.certificateInfo());
860 CompletionHandlerCallingScope completionHandlerCaller(WTFMove(completionHandler));
861
862#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
863 if (m_contentFilter && !m_contentFilter->continueAfterResponseReceived(response))
864 return;
865#endif
866
867 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
868 bool willLoadFallback = m_applicationCacheHost->maybeLoadFallbackForMainResponse(request(), response);
869
870 // The memory cache doesn't understand the application cache or its caching rules. So if a main resource is served
871 // from the application cache, ensure we don't save the result for future use.
872 if (willLoadFallback)
873 MemoryCache::singleton().remove(*m_mainResource);
874
875 if (willLoadFallback)
876 return;
877
878 ASSERT(m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader || m_mainResource);
879 unsigned long identifier = m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader ? m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader : m_mainResource->identifier();
880 ASSERT(identifier);
881
882 if (m_substituteData.isValid() || !platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->havePerformedSecurityChecks(response)) {
883 auto url = response.url();
884 ContentSecurityPolicy contentSecurityPolicy(URL { url }, this);
885 contentSecurityPolicy.didReceiveHeaders(ContentSecurityPolicyResponseHeaders { response }, m_request.httpReferrer());
886 if (!contentSecurityPolicy.allowFrameAncestors(*m_frame, url)) {
887 stopLoadingAfterXFrameOptionsOrContentSecurityPolicyDenied(identifier, response);
888 return;
889 }
890
891 if (!contentSecurityPolicy.overridesXFrameOptions()) {
892 String frameOptions = response.httpHeaderFields().get(HTTPHeaderName::XFrameOptions);
893 if (!frameOptions.isNull()) {
894 if (frameLoader()->shouldInterruptLoadForXFrameOptions(frameOptions, url, identifier)) {
895 String message = "Refused to display '" + url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "' in a frame because it set 'X-Frame-Options' to '" + frameOptions + "'.";
896 m_frame->document()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message, identifier);
897 stopLoadingAfterXFrameOptionsOrContentSecurityPolicyDenied(identifier, response);
898 return;
899 }
900 }
901 }
902 }
903
904 // There is a bug in CFNetwork where callbacks can be dispatched even when loads are deferred.
905 // See <rdar://problem/6304600> for more details.
906#if !USE(CF)
907 ASSERT(!mainResourceLoader() || !mainResourceLoader()->defersLoading());
908#endif
909
910 if (m_isLoadingMultipartContent) {
911 setupForReplace();
912 m_mainResource->clear();
913 } else if (response.isMultipart())
914 m_isLoadingMultipartContent = true;
915
916 m_response = response;
917
918 if (m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader) {
919 if (m_mainResource && m_mainResource->wasRedirected()) {
920 ASSERT(m_mainResource->status() == CachedResource::Status::Cached);
921 frameLoader()->client().dispatchDidReceiveServerRedirectForProvisionalLoad();
922 }
923 addResponse(m_response);
924 frameLoader()->notifier().dispatchDidReceiveResponse(this, m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, m_response, 0);
925 }
926
927 ASSERT(!m_waitingForContentPolicy);
928 ASSERT(frameLoader());
929 m_waitingForContentPolicy = true;
930
931 // Always show content with valid substitute data.
932 if (m_substituteData.isValid()) {
933 continueAfterContentPolicy(PolicyAction::Use);
934 return;
935 }
936
937#if ENABLE(FTPDIR)
938 // Respect the hidden FTP Directory Listing pref so it can be tested even if the policy delegate might otherwise disallow it
939 if (m_frame->settings().forceFTPDirectoryListings() && m_response.mimeType() == "application/x-ftp-directory") {
940 continueAfterContentPolicy(PolicyAction::Use);
941 return;
942 }
943#endif
944
945 RefPtr<SubresourceLoader> mainResourceLoader = this->mainResourceLoader();
946 if (mainResourceLoader)
947 mainResourceLoader->markInAsyncResponsePolicyCheck();
948 auto requestIdentifier = PolicyCheckIdentifier::create();
949 frameLoader()->checkContentPolicy(m_response, requestIdentifier, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), mainResourceLoader = WTFMove(mainResourceLoader),
950 completionHandler = completionHandlerCaller.release(), requestIdentifier] (PolicyAction policy, PolicyCheckIdentifier responseIdentifier) mutable {
951 RELEASE_ASSERT(responseIdentifier.isValidFor(requestIdentifier));
952 continueAfterContentPolicy(policy);
953 if (mainResourceLoader)
954 mainResourceLoader->didReceiveResponsePolicy();
955 if (completionHandler)
956 completionHandler();
957 });
958}
959
960// Prevent web archives from loading if
961// 1) it is remote;
962// 2) it is not the main frame;
963// 3) it is not any of { loaded by clients; loaded by drag; reloaded from any of the previous two };
964// because they can claim to be from any domain and thus avoid cross-domain security checks (4120255, 45524528, 47610130).
965bool DocumentLoader::disallowWebArchive() const
966{
967 using MIMETypeHashSet = HashSet<String, ASCIICaseInsensitiveHash>;
968 static NeverDestroyed<MIMETypeHashSet> webArchiveMIMETypes {
969 MIMETypeHashSet {
970 "application/x-webarchive"_s,
971 "application/x-mimearchive"_s,
972 "multipart/related"_s,
973#if PLATFORM(GTK)
974 "message/rfc822"_s,
975#endif
976 }
977 };
978
979 String mimeType = m_response.mimeType();
980 if (mimeType.isNull() || !webArchiveMIMETypes.get().contains(mimeType))
981 return false;
982
983#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
984 if (isQuickLookPreviewURL(m_response.url()))
985 return false;
986#endif
987
988 if (m_substituteData.isValid())
989 return false;
990
991 if (!LegacySchemeRegistry::shouldTreatURLSchemeAsLocal(m_request.url().protocol().toStringWithoutCopying()))
992 return true;
993
994 if (!frame() || (frame()->isMainFrame() && m_allowsWebArchiveForMainFrame))
995 return false;
996
997 // On purpose of maintaining existing tests.
998 if (frame()->mainFrame().loader().alwaysAllowLocalWebarchive())
999 return false;
1000 return true;
1001}
1002
1003// Prevent data URIs from loading as the main frame unless the result of user action.
1004bool DocumentLoader::disallowDataRequest() const
1005{
1006 if (!m_response.url().protocolIsData())
1007 return false;
1008
1009 if (!frame() || !frame()->isMainFrame() || m_allowsDataURLsForMainFrame || frame()->settings().allowTopNavigationToDataURLs())
1010 return false;
1011
1012 if (auto* currentDocument = frame()->document()) {
1013 unsigned long identifier = m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader ? m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader : m_mainResource->identifier();
1014 ASSERT(identifier);
1015
1016 currentDocument->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, makeString("Not allowed to navigate top frame to data URL '", m_response.url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength(), "'."), identifier);
1017 }
1018 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueAfterContentPolicy: cannot show URL");
1019
1020 return true;
1021}
1022
1023void DocumentLoader::continueAfterContentPolicy(PolicyAction policy)
1024{
1025 ASSERT(m_waitingForContentPolicy);
1026 m_waitingForContentPolicy = false;
1027 if (isStopping())
1028 return;
1029
1030 if (!m_frame) {
1031 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueAfterContentPolicy: policyAction=%i received by DocumentLoader with null frame", (int)policy);
1032 return;
1033 }
1034
1035 switch (policy) {
1036 case PolicyAction::Use: {
1037 if (!frameLoader()->client().canShowMIMEType(m_response.mimeType()) || disallowWebArchive() || disallowDataRequest()) {
1038 frameLoader()->policyChecker().cannotShowMIMEType(m_response);
1039 // Check reachedTerminalState since the load may have already been canceled inside of _handleUnimplementablePolicyWithErrorCode::.
1040 stopLoadingForPolicyChange();
1041 return;
1042 }
1043 break;
1044 }
1045
1046 case PolicyAction::Download: {
1047 // m_mainResource can be null, e.g. when loading a substitute resource from application cache.
1048 if (!m_mainResource) {
1049 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueAfterContentPolicy: cannot show URL");
1050 mainReceivedError(frameLoader()->client().cannotShowURLError(m_request));
1051 return;
1052 }
1053
1054 if (ResourceLoader* mainResourceLoader = this->mainResourceLoader())
1055 InspectorInstrumentation::continueWithPolicyDownload(*m_frame, mainResourceLoader->identifier(), *this, m_response);
1056
1057 // When starting the request, we didn't know that it would result in download and not navigation. Now we know that main document URL didn't change.
1058 // Download may use this knowledge for purposes unrelated to cookies, notably for setting file quarantine data.
1059 frameLoader()->setOriginalURLForDownloadRequest(m_request);
1060
1061 if (m_request.url().protocolIsData()) {
1062 // We decode data URL internally, there is no resource load to convert.
1063 frameLoader()->client().startDownload(m_request);
1064 } else
1065 frameLoader()->client().convertMainResourceLoadToDownload(this, m_request, m_response);
1066
1067 // The main resource might be loading from the memory cache, or its loader might have gone missing.
1068 if (mainResourceLoader()) {
1069 static_cast<ResourceLoader*>(mainResourceLoader())->didFail(interruptedForPolicyChangeError());
1070 return;
1071 }
1072
1073 // We must stop loading even if there is no main resource loader. Otherwise, we might remain
1074 // the client of a CachedRawResource that will continue to send us data.
1075 stopLoadingForPolicyChange();
1076 return;
1077 }
1078 case PolicyAction::StopAllLoads:
1079 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1080#if !ASSERT_ENABLED
1081 FALLTHROUGH;
1082#endif
1083 case PolicyAction::Ignore:
1084 if (ResourceLoader* mainResourceLoader = this->mainResourceLoader())
1085 InspectorInstrumentation::continueWithPolicyIgnore(*m_frame, mainResourceLoader->identifier(), *this, m_response);
1086 stopLoadingForPolicyChange();
1087 return;
1088 }
1089
1090 if (m_response.isInHTTPFamily()) {
1091 int status = m_response.httpStatusCode(); // Status may be zero when loading substitute data, in particular from a WebArchive.
1092 if (status && (status < 200 || status >= 300)) {
1093 auto* owner = m_frame->ownerElement();
1094 if (is<HTMLObjectElement>(owner)) {
1095 downcast<HTMLObjectElement>(*owner).renderFallbackContent();
1096 // object elements are no longer rendered after we fallback, so don't
1097 // keep trying to process data from their load
1098 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->cancelledError(m_request));
1099 }
1100 }
1101 }
1102
1103 if (!isStopping() && m_substituteData.isValid() && isLoadingMainResource()) {
1104 auto content = m_substituteData.content();
1105 if (content && content->size()) {
1106 content->forEachSegment([&](auto& segment) {
1107 dataReceived(segment.data(), segment.size());
1108 });
1109 }
1110 if (isLoadingMainResource())
1111 finishedLoading();
1112
1113 // Remove ourselves as a client of this CachedResource as we've decided to commit substitute data but the
1114 // load may keep going and be useful to other clients of the CachedResource. If we did not do this, we
1115 // may receive data later on even though this DocumentLoader has finished loading.
1116 clearMainResource();
1117 }
1118}
1119
1120void DocumentLoader::commitLoad(const uint8_t* data, int length)
1121{
1122 // Both unloading the old page and parsing the new page may execute JavaScript which destroys the datasource
1123 // by starting a new load, so retain temporarily.
1124 RefPtr<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame.get());
1125 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
1126
1127 commitIfReady();
1128 FrameLoader* frameLoader = DocumentLoader::frameLoader();
1129 if (!frameLoader)
1130 return;
1131#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
1132 if (ArchiveFactory::isArchiveMIMEType(response().mimeType()))
1133 return;
1134#endif
1135 frameLoader->client().committedLoad(this, data, length);
1136
1137 if (isMultipartReplacingLoad())
1138 frameLoader->client().didReplaceMultipartContent();
1139}
1140
1141ResourceError DocumentLoader::interruptedForPolicyChangeError() const
1142{
1143 if (!frameLoader())
1144 return {};
1145
1146 return frameLoader()->client().interruptedForPolicyChangeError(request());
1147}
1148
1149void DocumentLoader::stopLoadingForPolicyChange()
1150{
1151 ResourceError error = interruptedForPolicyChangeError();
1152 error.setType(ResourceError::Type::Cancellation);
1153 cancelMainResourceLoad(error);
1154}
1155
1156#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1157// https://w3c.github.io/ServiceWorker/#control-and-use-window-client
1158static inline bool shouldUseActiveServiceWorkerFromParent(const Document& document, const Document& parent)
1159{
1160 return !document.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily() && !document.securityOrigin().isUnique() && parent.securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(document.securityOrigin());
1161}
1162#endif
1163
1164void DocumentLoader::commitData(const uint8_t* bytes, size_t length)
1165{
1166 if (!m_gotFirstByte) {
1167 m_gotFirstByte = true;
1168 bool hasBegun = m_writer.begin(documentURL(), false);
1169 if (!hasBegun)
1170 return;
1171
1172 m_writer.setDocumentWasLoadedAsPartOfNavigation();
1173
1174 auto* documentOrNull = m_frame ? m_frame->document() : nullptr;
1175 if (!documentOrNull)
1176 return;
1177 auto& document = *documentOrNull;
1178
1179 if (SecurityPolicy::allowSubstituteDataAccessToLocal() && m_originalSubstituteDataWasValid) {
1180 // If this document was loaded with substituteData, then the document can
1181 // load local resources. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=16756
1182 // and https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=19760 for further
1183 // discussion.
1184 document.securityOrigin().grantLoadLocalResources();
1185 }
1186
1187 if (frameLoader()->stateMachine().creatingInitialEmptyDocument())
1188 return;
1189
1190#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
1191 if (m_archive && m_archive->shouldOverrideBaseURL())
1192 document.setBaseURLOverride(m_archive->mainResource()->url());
1193#endif
1194#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1195 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled()) {
1196 if (m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData && m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData->activeWorker) {
1197 document.setActiveServiceWorker(ServiceWorker::getOrCreate(document, WTFMove(m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData->activeWorker.value())));
1198 m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData = { };
1199 } else if (auto* parent = document.parentDocument()) {
1200 if (shouldUseActiveServiceWorkerFromParent(document, *parent))
1201 document.setActiveServiceWorker(parent->activeServiceWorker());
1202 }
1203
1204 if (m_frame->document()->activeServiceWorker() || document.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily())
1205 document.setServiceWorkerConnection(&ServiceWorkerProvider::singleton().serviceWorkerConnection());
1206
1207 // We currently unregister the temporary service worker client since we now registered the real document.
1208 // FIXME: We should make the real document use the temporary client identifier.
1209 unregisterTemporaryServiceWorkerClient();
1210 }
1211#endif
1212 // Call receivedFirstData() exactly once per load. We should only reach this point multiple times
1213 // for multipart loads, and FrameLoader::isReplacing() will be true after the first time.
1214 if (!isMultipartReplacingLoad())
1215 frameLoader()->receivedFirstData();
1216
1217 // The load could be canceled under receivedFirstData(), which makes delegate calls and even sometimes dispatches DOM events.
1218 if (!isLoading())
1219 return;
1220
1221 if (auto* window = document.domWindow())
1222 window->prewarmLocalStorageIfNecessary();
1223
1224 bool userChosen;
1225 String encoding;
1226 if (overrideEncoding().isNull()) {
1227 userChosen = false;
1228 encoding = response().textEncodingName();
1229#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
1230 if (m_archive && m_archive->shouldUseMainResourceEncoding())
1231 encoding = m_archive->mainResource()->textEncoding();
1232#endif
1233 } else {
1234 userChosen = true;
1235 encoding = overrideEncoding();
1236 }
1237
1238 m_writer.setEncoding(encoding, userChosen);
1239 }
1240
1241#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
1242 auto& extensionStyleSheets = m_frame->document()->extensionStyleSheets();
1243
1244 for (auto& pendingStyleSheet : m_pendingNamedContentExtensionStyleSheets)
1245 extensionStyleSheets.maybeAddContentExtensionSheet(pendingStyleSheet.key, *pendingStyleSheet.value);
1246 for (auto& pendingSelectorEntry : m_pendingContentExtensionDisplayNoneSelectors) {
1247 for (const auto& pendingSelector : pendingSelectorEntry.value)
1248 extensionStyleSheets.addDisplayNoneSelector(pendingSelectorEntry.key, pendingSelector.first, pendingSelector.second);
1249 }
1250
1251 m_pendingNamedContentExtensionStyleSheets.clear();
1252 m_pendingContentExtensionDisplayNoneSelectors.clear();
1253#endif
1254
1255 ASSERT(m_frame->document()->parsing());
1256 m_writer.addData(bytes, length);
1257}
1258
1259void DocumentLoader::dataReceived(CachedResource& resource, const uint8_t* data, int length)
1260{
1261 ASSERT_UNUSED(resource, &resource == m_mainResource);
1262 dataReceived(data, length);
1263}
1264
1265void DocumentLoader::dataReceived(const uint8_t* data, int length)
1266{
1267#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
1268 if (m_contentFilter && !m_contentFilter->continueAfterDataReceived(data, length))
1269 return;
1270#endif
1271
1272 ASSERT(data);
1273 ASSERT(length);
1274 ASSERT(!m_response.isNull());
1275
1276 // There is a bug in CFNetwork where callbacks can be dispatched even when loads are deferred.
1277 // See <rdar://problem/6304600> for more details.
1278#if !USE(CF)
1279 ASSERT(!mainResourceLoader() || !mainResourceLoader()->defersLoading());
1280#endif
1281
1282 if (m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader)
1283 frameLoader()->notifier().dispatchDidReceiveData(this, m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, data, length, -1);
1284
1285 m_applicationCacheHost->mainResourceDataReceived(data, length, -1, false);
1286
1287 if (!isMultipartReplacingLoad())
1288 commitLoad(data, length);
1289}
1290
1291void DocumentLoader::setupForReplace()
1292{
1293 if (!mainResourceData())
1294 return;
1295
1296 frameLoader()->client().willReplaceMultipartContent();
1297
1298 maybeFinishLoadingMultipartContent();
1299 maybeCreateArchive();
1300 m_writer.end();
1301 frameLoader()->setReplacing();
1302 m_gotFirstByte = false;
1303
1304 stopLoadingSubresources();
1305 stopLoadingPlugIns();
1306#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
1307 clearArchiveResources();
1308#endif
1309}
1310
1311void DocumentLoader::checkLoadComplete()
1312{
1313 if (!m_frame || isLoading())
1314 return;
1315
1316 ASSERT(this == frameLoader()->activeDocumentLoader());
1317 m_frame->document()->domWindow()->finishedLoading();
1318}
1319
1320void DocumentLoader::applyPoliciesToSettings()
1321{
1322 if (!m_frame) {
1323 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1324 return;
1325 }
1326
1327 if (!m_frame->isMainFrame())
1328 return;
1329
1330#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SOURCE)
1331 m_frame->settings().setMediaSourceEnabled(m_mediaSourcePolicy == MediaSourcePolicy::Default ? Settings::platformDefaultMediaSourceEnabled() : m_mediaSourcePolicy == MediaSourcePolicy::Enable);
1332#endif
1333#if ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
1334 m_frame->settings().setIdempotentModeAutosizingOnlyHonorsPercentages(m_idempotentModeAutosizingOnlyHonorsPercentages);
1335#endif
1336#if USE(APPLE_INTERNAL_SDK)
1337 updateAdditionalSettingsIfNeeded();
1338#endif
1339}
1340
1341MouseEventPolicy DocumentLoader::mouseEventPolicy() const
1342{
1343#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
1344 if (m_mouseEventPolicy == MouseEventPolicy::Default) {
1345 if (auto* document = this->document()) {
1346 if (document->quirks().shouldSynthesizeTouchEvents())
1347 return MouseEventPolicy::SynthesizeTouchEvents;
1348 }
1349 }
1350#endif
1351 return m_mouseEventPolicy;
1352}
1353
1354void DocumentLoader::attachToFrame(Frame& frame)
1355{
1356 if (m_frame == &frame)
1357 return;
1358
1359 ASSERT(!m_frame);
1360 observeFrame(&frame);
1361 m_writer.setFrame(frame);
1362 attachToFrame();
1363
1364#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1365 m_hasEverBeenAttached = true;
1366#endif
1367
1368 applyPoliciesToSettings();
1369}
1370
1371void DocumentLoader::attachToFrame()
1372{
1373 ASSERT(m_frame);
1374 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("DocumentLoader::attachToFrame: m_frame=%p", m_frame.get());
1375}
1376
1377void DocumentLoader::detachFromFrame()
1378{
1379 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("DocumentLoader::detachFromFrame: m_frame=%p", m_frame.get());
1380
1381#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1382 if (m_hasEverBeenAttached)
1383 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_frame, "detachFromFrame() is being called on a DocumentLoader twice without an attachToFrame() inbetween");
1384 else
1385 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_frame, "detachFromFrame() is being called on a DocumentLoader that has never attached to any Frame");
1386#endif
1387 RefPtr<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame.get());
1388 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
1389
1390 // It never makes sense to have a document loader that is detached from its
1391 // frame have any loads active, so kill all the loads.
1392 stopLoading();
1393 if (m_mainResource && m_mainResource->hasClient(*this))
1394 m_mainResource->removeClient(*this);
1395#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
1396 if (m_contentFilter)
1397 m_contentFilter->stopFilteringMainResource();
1398#endif
1399
1400 m_applicationCacheHost->setDOMApplicationCache(nullptr);
1401
1402 cancelPolicyCheckIfNeeded();
1403
1404 // cancelPolicyCheckIfNeeded can clear m_frame if the policy check
1405 // is stopped, resulting in a recursive call into this detachFromFrame.
1406 // If m_frame is nullptr after cancelPolicyCheckIfNeeded, our work is
1407 // already done so just return.
1408 if (!m_frame)
1409 return;
1410
1411 InspectorInstrumentation::loaderDetachedFromFrame(*m_frame, *this);
1412
1413 observeFrame(nullptr);
1414}
1415
1416void DocumentLoader::clearMainResourceLoader()
1417{
1418 m_loadingMainResource = false;
1419
1420 auto* frameLoader = this->frameLoader();
1421
1422 if (!frameLoader)
1423 return;
1424
1425 if (this == frameLoader->activeDocumentLoader())
1426 checkLoadComplete();
1427}
1428
1429#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
1430uint64_t DocumentLoader::loadApplicationManifest()
1431{
1432 static uint64_t nextCallbackID = 1;
1433
1434 auto* document = this->document();
1435 if (!document)
1436 return 0;
1437
1438 if (!m_frame->isMainFrame())
1439 return 0;
1440
1441 if (document->url().isEmpty() || document->url().protocolIsAbout())
1442 return 0;
1443
1444 auto head = document->head();
1445 if (!head)
1446 return 0;
1447
1448 URL manifestURL;
1449 bool useCredentials = false;
1450 for (const auto& link : childrenOfType<HTMLLinkElement>(*head)) {
1451 if (link.isApplicationManifest()) {
1452 manifestURL = link.href();
1453 useCredentials = equalIgnoringASCIICase(link.attributeWithoutSynchronization(HTMLNames::crossoriginAttr), "use-credentials");
1454 break;
1455 }
1456 }
1457
1458 if (manifestURL.isEmpty() || !manifestURL.isValid())
1459 return 0;
1460
1461 auto manifestLoader = makeUnique<ApplicationManifestLoader>(*this, manifestURL, useCredentials);
1462 auto* rawManifestLoader = manifestLoader.get();
1463 auto callbackID = nextCallbackID++;
1464 m_applicationManifestLoaders.set(WTFMove(manifestLoader), callbackID);
1465
1466 if (!rawManifestLoader->startLoading()) {
1467 m_applicationManifestLoaders.remove(rawManifestLoader);
1468 return 0;
1469 }
1470
1471 return callbackID;
1472}
1473
1474void DocumentLoader::finishedLoadingApplicationManifest(ApplicationManifestLoader& loader)
1475{
1476 // If the DocumentLoader has detached from its frame, all manifest loads should have already been canceled.
1477 ASSERT(m_frame);
1478
1479 auto callbackIdentifier = m_applicationManifestLoaders.get(&loader);
1480 notifyFinishedLoadingApplicationManifest(callbackIdentifier, loader.processManifest());
1481 m_applicationManifestLoaders.remove(&loader);
1482}
1483
1484void DocumentLoader::notifyFinishedLoadingApplicationManifest(uint64_t callbackIdentifier, std::optional<ApplicationManifest> manifest)
1485{
1486 RELEASE_ASSERT(callbackIdentifier);
1487 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_frame);
1488 m_frame->loader().client().finishedLoadingApplicationManifest(callbackIdentifier, manifest);
1489}
1490#endif
1491
1492bool DocumentLoader::isLoadingInAPISense() const
1493{
1494 // Once a frame has loaded, we no longer need to consider subresources,
1495 // but we still need to consider subframes.
1496 if (frameLoader()->state() != FrameState::Complete) {
1497 ASSERT(m_frame->document());
1498 auto& document = *m_frame->document();
1499 if ((isLoadingMainResource() || !document.loadEventFinished()) && isLoading())
1500 return true;
1501 if (m_cachedResourceLoader->requestCount())
1502 return true;
1503 if (document.isDelayingLoadEvent())
1504 return true;
1505 if (document.processingLoadEvent())
1506 return true;
1507 if (document.hasActiveParser())
1508 return true;
1509 auto* scriptableParser = document.scriptableDocumentParser();
1510 if (scriptableParser && scriptableParser->hasScriptsWaitingForStylesheets())
1511 return true;
1512 }
1513 return frameLoader()->subframeIsLoading();
1514}
1515
1516bool DocumentLoader::maybeCreateArchive()
1517{
1518#if !ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) && !ENABLE(MHTML)
1519 return false;
1520#else
1521 // Give the archive machinery a crack at this document. If the MIME type is not an archive type, it will return 0.
1522 m_archive = ArchiveFactory::create(m_response.url(), mainResourceData().get(), m_response.mimeType());
1523 if (!m_archive)
1524 return false;
1525
1526 addAllArchiveResources(*m_archive);
1527 ASSERT(m_archive->mainResource());
1528 auto& mainResource = *m_archive->mainResource();
1529 m_parsedArchiveData = &mainResource.data();
1530 m_writer.setMIMEType(mainResource.mimeType());
1531
1532 ASSERT(m_frame->document());
1533 commitData(mainResource.data().data(), mainResource.data().size());
1534 return true;
1535#endif
1536}

1590RefPtr<ArchiveResource> DocumentLoader::mainResource() const
1591{
1592 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> data = mainResourceData();
1593 if (!data)
1594 data = SharedBuffer::create();
1595 auto& response = this->response();
1596 return ArchiveResource::create(WTFMove(data), response.url(), response.mimeType(), response.textEncodingName(), frame()->tree().uniqueName());
1597}
1598
1599RefPtr<ArchiveResource> DocumentLoader::subresource(const URL& url) const
1600{
1601 if (!isCommitted())
1602 return nullptr;
1603
1604 auto* resource = m_cachedResourceLoader->cachedResource(url);
1605 if (!resource || !resource->isLoaded())
1606 return archiveResourceForURL(url);
1607
1608 if (resource->type() == CachedResource::Type::MainResource)
1609 return nullptr;
1610
1611 auto* data = resource->resourceBuffer();
1612 if (!data)
1613 return nullptr;
1614
1615 return ArchiveResource::create(data, url, resource->response());
1616}
1617
1618Vector<Ref<ArchiveResource>> DocumentLoader::subresources() const
1619{
1620 if (!isCommitted())
1621 return { };
1622
1623 Vector<Ref<ArchiveResource>> subresources;
1624 for (auto& handle : m_cachedResourceLoader->allCachedResources().values()) {
1625 if (auto subresource = this->subresource(handle->url()))
1626 subresources.append(subresource.releaseNonNull());
1627 }
1628 return subresources;
1629}
1630
1631void DocumentLoader::deliverSubstituteResourcesAfterDelay()
1632{
1633 if (m_pendingSubstituteResources.isEmpty())
1634 return;
1635 ASSERT(m_frame);
1636 ASSERT(m_frame->page());
1637 if (m_frame->page()->defersLoading())
1638 return;
1639
1640 if (!m_substituteResourceDeliveryTimer.isActive())
1641 m_substituteResourceDeliveryTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
1642}
1643
1644void DocumentLoader::substituteResourceDeliveryTimerFired()
1645{
1646 if (m_pendingSubstituteResources.isEmpty())
1647 return;
1648 ASSERT(m_frame);
1649 ASSERT(m_frame->page());
1650 if (m_frame->page()->defersLoading())
1651 return;
1652
1653 auto pendingSubstituteResources = WTFMove(m_pendingSubstituteResources);
1654 for (auto& pendingSubstituteResource : pendingSubstituteResources) {
1655 auto& loader = pendingSubstituteResource.key;
1656 if (auto& resource = pendingSubstituteResource.value)
1657 resource->deliver(*loader);
1658 else {
1659 // A null resource means that we should fail the load.
1660 // FIXME: Maybe we should use another error here - something like "not in cache".
1661 loader->didFail(loader->cannotShowURLError());
1662 }
1663 }
1664}
1665

1667
1668bool DocumentLoader::isSubstituteLoadPending(ResourceLoader* loader) const
1669{
1670 return m_pendingSubstituteResources.contains(loader);
1671}
1672
1673#endif // ASSERT_ENABLED

1675void DocumentLoader::cancelPendingSubstituteLoad(ResourceLoader* loader)
1676{
1677 if (m_pendingSubstituteResources.isEmpty())
1678 return;
1679 m_pendingSubstituteResources.remove(loader);
1680 if (m_pendingSubstituteResources.isEmpty())
1681 m_substituteResourceDeliveryTimer.stop();
1682}

1684#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
1685
1686bool DocumentLoader::scheduleArchiveLoad(ResourceLoader& loader, const ResourceRequest& request)
1687{
1688 if (auto* resource = archiveResourceForURL(request.url())) {
1689 scheduleSubstituteResourceLoad(loader, *resource);
1690 return true;
1691 }
1692
1693 if (!m_archive)
1694 return false;
1695
1696#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE)
1697 // The idea of WebArchiveDebugMode is that we should fail instead of trying to fetch from the network.
1698 // Returning true ensures the caller will not try to fetch from the network.
1699 if (m_frame->settings().webArchiveDebugModeEnabled() && responseMIMEType() == "application/x-webarchive")
1700 return true;
1701#endif
1702
1703 // If we want to load from the archive only, then we should always return true so that the caller
1704 // does not try to fetch form the network.
1705 return m_archive->shouldLoadFromArchiveOnly();
1706}
1707
1708#endif
1709
1710void DocumentLoader::scheduleSubstituteResourceLoad(ResourceLoader& loader, SubstituteResource& resource)
1711{
1712#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1713 ASSERT(!loader.options().serviceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier);
1714#endif
1715 m_pendingSubstituteResources.set(&loader, &resource);
1716 deliverSubstituteResourcesAfterDelay();
1717}
1718
1719void DocumentLoader::scheduleCannotShowURLError(ResourceLoader& loader)
1720{
1721 m_pendingSubstituteResources.set(&loader, nullptr);
1722 deliverSubstituteResourcesAfterDelay();
1723}

1753URL DocumentLoader::urlForHistory() const
1754{
1755 // Return the URL to be used for history and B/F list.
1756 // Returns nil for WebDataProtocol URLs that aren't alternates
1757 // for unreachable URLs, because these can't be stored in history.
1758 if (m_substituteData.isValid() && !m_substituteData.shouldRevealToSessionHistory())
1759 return unreachableURL();
1760
1761 return m_originalRequestCopy.url();
1762}

1764bool DocumentLoader::urlForHistoryReflectsFailure() const
1765{
1766 return m_substituteData.isValid() || m_response.httpStatusCode() >= 400;
1767}
1768
1769URL DocumentLoader::documentURL() const
1770{
1771 URL url = substituteData().response().url();
1772#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE)
1773 if (url.isEmpty() && m_archive && m_archive->shouldUseMainResourceURL())
1774 url = m_archive->mainResource()->url();
1775#endif
1776 if (url.isEmpty())
1777 url = m_request.url();
1778 if (url.isEmpty())
1779 url = m_response.url();
1780 return url;
1781}

1792
1793void DocumentLoader::setDefersLoading(bool defers)
1794{
1795 // Multiple frames may be loading the same main resource simultaneously. If deferral state changes,
1796 // each frame's DocumentLoader will try to send a setDefersLoading() to the same underlying ResourceLoader. Ensure only
1797 // the "owning" DocumentLoader does so, as setDefersLoading() is not resilient to setting the same value repeatedly.
1798 if (mainResourceLoader() && mainResourceLoader()->documentLoader() == this)
1799 mainResourceLoader()->setDefersLoading(defers);
1800
1801 setAllDefersLoading(m_subresourceLoaders, defers);
1802 setAllDefersLoading(m_plugInStreamLoaders, defers);
1803 if (!defers)
1804 deliverSubstituteResourcesAfterDelay();
1805}

1807void DocumentLoader::setMainResourceDataBufferingPolicy(DataBufferingPolicy dataBufferingPolicy)
1808{
1809 if (m_mainResource)
1810 m_mainResource->setDataBufferingPolicy(dataBufferingPolicy);
1811}

1813void DocumentLoader::stopLoadingPlugIns()
1814{
1815 cancelAll(m_plugInStreamLoaders);
1816}
1817
1818void DocumentLoader::stopLoadingSubresources()
1819{
1820 cancelAll(m_subresourceLoaders);
1821 ASSERT(m_subresourceLoaders.isEmpty());
1822}
1823
1824void DocumentLoader::addSubresourceLoader(ResourceLoader* loader)
1825{
1826 // The main resource's underlying ResourceLoader will ask to be added here.
1827 // It is much simpler to handle special casing of main resource loads if we don't
1828 // let it be added. In the main resource load case, mainResourceLoader()
1829 // will still be null at this point, but m_gotFirstByte should be false here if and only
1830 // if we are just starting the main resource load.
1831 if (!m_gotFirstByte)
1832 return;
1833 ASSERT(loader->identifier());
1834 ASSERT(!m_subresourceLoaders.contains(loader->identifier()));
1835 ASSERT(!mainResourceLoader() || mainResourceLoader() != loader);
1836
1837 // Application Cache loaders are handled by their ApplicationCacheGroup directly.
1838 if (loader->options().applicationCacheMode == ApplicationCacheMode::Bypass)
1839 return;
1840
1841#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1842 if (document()) {
1843 switch (document()->backForwardCacheState()) {
1844 case Document::NotInBackForwardCache:
1845 break;
1846 case Document::AboutToEnterBackForwardCache: {
1847 // A page about to enter the BackForwardCache should only be able to start ping loads.
1848 auto* cachedResource = downcast<SubresourceLoader>(loader)->cachedResource();
1849 ASSERT(cachedResource && (CachedResource::shouldUsePingLoad(cachedResource->type()) || cachedResource->options().keepAlive));
1850 break;
1851 }
1852 case Document::InBackForwardCache:
1853 // A page in the BackForwardCache should not be able to start loads.
1854 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1855 break;
1856 }
1857 }
1858#endif
1859
1860 m_subresourceLoaders.add(loader->identifier(), loader);
1861}
1862
1863void DocumentLoader::removeSubresourceLoader(LoadCompletionType type, ResourceLoader* loader)
1864{
1865 ASSERT(loader->identifier());
1866
1867 if (!m_subresourceLoaders.remove(loader->identifier()))
1868 return;
1869 checkLoadComplete();
1870 if (m_frame)
1871 m_frame->loader().subresourceLoadDone(type);
1872}
1873
1874void DocumentLoader::addPlugInStreamLoader(ResourceLoader& loader)
1875{
1876 ASSERT(loader.identifier());
1877 ASSERT(!m_plugInStreamLoaders.contains(loader.identifier()));
1878
1879 m_plugInStreamLoaders.add(loader.identifier(), &loader);
1880}
1881
1882void DocumentLoader::removePlugInStreamLoader(ResourceLoader& loader)
1883{
1884 ASSERT(loader.identifier());
1885 ASSERT(&loader == m_plugInStreamLoaders.get(loader.identifier()));
1886
1887 m_plugInStreamLoaders.remove(loader.identifier());
1888 checkLoadComplete();
1889}

1891bool DocumentLoader::isMultipartReplacingLoad() const

1893 return isLoadingMultipartContent() && frameLoader()->isReplacing();
1894}
1895
1896bool DocumentLoader::maybeLoadEmpty()
1897{
1898 bool shouldLoadEmpty = !m_substituteData.isValid() && (m_request.url().isEmpty() || LegacySchemeRegistry::shouldLoadURLSchemeAsEmptyDocument(m_request.url().protocol().toStringWithoutCopying()));
1899 if (!shouldLoadEmpty && !frameLoader()->client().representationExistsForURLScheme(m_request.url().protocol().toStringWithoutCopying()))
1900 return false;
1901
1902 if (m_request.url().isEmpty() && !frameLoader()->stateMachine().creatingInitialEmptyDocument()) {
1903 m_request.setURL(aboutBlankURL());
1904 if (isLoadingMainResource())
1905 frameLoader()->client().dispatchDidChangeProvisionalURL();
1906 }
1907
1908 String mimeType = shouldLoadEmpty ? "text/html" : frameLoader()->client().generatedMIMETypeForURLScheme(m_request.url().protocol().toStringWithoutCopying());
1909 m_response = ResourceResponse(m_request.url(), mimeType, 0, "UTF-8"_s);
1910 finishedLoading();
1911 return true;
1912}
1913
1914void DocumentLoader::startLoadingMainResource()
1915{
1916 m_mainDocumentError = ResourceError();
1917 timing().markStartTime();
1918 ASSERT(!m_mainResource);
1919 ASSERT(!m_loadingMainResource);
1920 m_loadingMainResource = true;
1921
1922 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
1923
1924 if (maybeLoadEmpty()) {
1925 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource: Returning empty document");
1926 return;
1927 }
1928
1929#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
1930 m_contentFilter = !m_substituteData.isValid() ? ContentFilter::create(*this) : nullptr;
1931#endif
1932
1933 // Make sure we re-apply the user agent to the Document's ResourceRequest upon reload in case the embedding
1934 // application has changed it, by clearing the previous user agent value here and applying the new value in CachedResourceLoader.
1935 m_request.clearHTTPUserAgent();
1936
1937 ASSERT(timing().startTime());
1938
1939 willSendRequest(ResourceRequest(m_request), ResourceResponse(), [this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis)] (ResourceRequest&& request) mutable {
1940 m_request = request;
1941 // FIXME: Implement local URL interception by getting the service worker of the parent.
1942
1943 // willSendRequest() may lead to our Frame being detached or cancelling the load via nulling the ResourceRequest.
1944 if (!m_frame || m_request.isNull()) {
1945 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource: Load canceled after willSendRequest");
1946 return;
1947 }
1948
1949 request.setRequester(ResourceRequest::Requester::Main);
1950 // If this is a reload the cache layer might have made the previous request conditional. DocumentLoader can't handle 304 responses itself.
1951 request.makeUnconditional();
1952
1953 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource: Starting load");
1954
1955#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1956 if (m_applicationCacheHost->canLoadMainResource(request) || m_substituteData.isValid()) {
1957 auto url = request.url();
1958 matchRegistration(url, [request = WTFMove(request), protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), this] (auto&& registrationData) mutable {
1959 if (!m_mainDocumentError.isNull()) {
1960 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource callback: Load canceled because of main document error (type=%d, code=%d)", static_cast<int>(m_mainDocumentError.type()), m_mainDocumentError.errorCode());
1961 return;
1962 }
1963 if (!m_frame) {
1964 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource callback: Load canceled because no frame");
1965 return;
1966 }
1967
1968 m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData = WTFMove(registrationData);
1969 // Prefer existing substitute data (from WKWebView.loadData etc) over service worker fetch.
1970 if (this->tryLoadingSubstituteData()) {
1971 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource callback: Load canceled because of substitute data");
1972 return;
1973 }
1974
1975 if (!m_serviceWorkerRegistrationData && this->tryLoadingRequestFromApplicationCache()) {
1976 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource callback: Loaded from Application Cache");
1977 return;
1978 }
1979 this->loadMainResource(WTFMove(request));
1980 });
1981 return;
1982 }
1983#else
1984 if (tryLoadingRequestFromApplicationCache()) {
1985 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startLoadingMainResource: Loaded from Application Cache");
1986 return;
1987 }
1988#endif
1989 loadMainResource(WTFMove(request));
1990 });
1991}
1992
1993void DocumentLoader::unregisterTemporaryServiceWorkerClient()
1994{
1995#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1996 if (!m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient || !RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled())
1997 return;
1998
1999 auto& serviceWorkerConnection = ServiceWorkerProvider::singleton().serviceWorkerConnection();
2000 serviceWorkerConnection.unregisterServiceWorkerClient(*m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient);
2001#endif
2002}
2003
2004void DocumentLoader::loadMainResource(ResourceRequest&& request)
2005{
2006 ResourceLoaderOptions mainResourceLoadOptions(
2007 SendCallbackPolicy::SendCallbacks,
2008 ContentSniffingPolicy::SniffContent,
2009 DataBufferingPolicy::BufferData,
2010 StoredCredentialsPolicy::Use,
2011 ClientCredentialPolicy::MayAskClientForCredentials,
2012 FetchOptions::Credentials::Include,
2013 SecurityCheckPolicy::SkipSecurityCheck,
2014 FetchOptions::Mode::Navigate,
2015 CertificateInfoPolicy::IncludeCertificateInfo,
2016 ContentSecurityPolicyImposition::SkipPolicyCheck,
2017 DefersLoadingPolicy::AllowDefersLoading,
2018 CachingPolicy::AllowCaching);
2019#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
2020 if (!m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient) {
2021 // The main navigation load will trigger the registration of the temp client.
2022 m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient = DocumentIdentifier::generate();
2023 ASSERT(!temporaryIdentifierToLoaderMap().contains(*m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient));
2024 temporaryIdentifierToLoaderMap().add(*m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient, this);
2025 }
2026 mainResourceLoadOptions.clientIdentifier = m_temporaryServiceWorkerClient;
2027#endif
2028 CachedResourceRequest mainResourceRequest(WTFMove(request), mainResourceLoadOptions);
2029 if (!m_frame->isMainFrame() && m_frame->document()) {
2030 // If we are loading the main resource of a subframe, use the cache partition of the main document.
2031 mainResourceRequest.setDomainForCachePartition(*m_frame->document());
2032 } else {
2033 auto origin = SecurityOrigin::create(mainResourceRequest.resourceRequest().url());
2034 origin->setStorageBlockingPolicy(frameLoader()->frame().settings().storageBlockingPolicy());
2035 mainResourceRequest.setDomainForCachePartition(origin->domainForCachePartition());
2036 }
2037
2038 m_mainResource = m_cachedResourceLoader->requestMainResource(WTFMove(mainResourceRequest)).value_or(nullptr);
2039
2040 if (!m_mainResource) {
2041 // The frame may have gone away if this load was cancelled synchronously and this was the last pending load.
2042 // This is because we may have fired the load event in a parent frame.
2043 if (!m_frame) {
2044 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("loadMainResource: Unable to load main resource, frame has gone away");
2045 return;
2046 }
2047
2048 if (!m_request.url().isValid()) {
2049 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("loadMainResource: Unable to load main resource, URL is invalid");
2050 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->client().cannotShowURLError(m_request));
2051 return;
2052 }
2053
2054 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("loadMainResource: Unable to load main resource, returning empty document");
2055
2056 setRequest(ResourceRequest());
2057 // If the load was aborted by clearing m_request, it's possible the ApplicationCacheHost
2058 // is now in a state where starting an empty load will be inconsistent. Replace it with
2059 // a new ApplicationCacheHost.
2060 m_applicationCacheHost = makeUnique<ApplicationCacheHost>(*this);
2061 maybeLoadEmpty();
2062 return;
2063 }
2064
2065 ASSERT(m_frame);
2066
2067#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
2068 if (m_mainResource->errorOccurred() && m_frame->page() && m_mainResource->resourceError().domain() == ContentExtensions::WebKitContentBlockerDomain) {
2069 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("loadMainResource: Blocked by content blocker error");
2070 cancelMainResourceLoad(frameLoader()->blockedByContentBlockerError(m_request));
2071 return;
2072 }
2073#endif
2074
2075 if (!mainResourceLoader()) {
2076 m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader = m_frame->page()->progress().createUniqueIdentifier();
2077 frameLoader()->notifier().assignIdentifierToInitialRequest(m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, this, mainResourceRequest.resourceRequest());
2078 frameLoader()->notifier().dispatchWillSendRequest(this, m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader, mainResourceRequest.resourceRequest(), ResourceResponse(), nullptr);
2079 }
2080
2081 becomeMainResourceClient();
2082
2083 // A bunch of headers are set when the underlying ResourceLoader is created, and m_request needs to include those.
2084 ResourceRequest updatedRequest = mainResourceLoader() ? mainResourceLoader()->originalRequest() : mainResourceRequest.resourceRequest();
2085 // If there was a fragment identifier on m_request, the cache will have stripped it. m_request should include
2086 // the fragment identifier, so add that back in.
2087 if (equalIgnoringFragmentIdentifier(m_request.url(), updatedRequest.url()))
2088 updatedRequest.setURL(m_request.url());
2089 setRequest(updatedRequest);
2090}

2097 m_waitingForContentPolicy = false;

2102void DocumentLoader::cancelMainResourceLoad(const ResourceError& resourceError)
2103{
2104 Ref<DocumentLoader> protectedThis(*this);
2105 ResourceError error = resourceError.isNull() ? frameLoader()->cancelledError(m_request) : resourceError;
2106
2107 DOCUMENTLOADER_RELEASE_LOG("cancelMainResourceLoad: (type=%d, code=%d)", static_cast<int>(error.type()), error.errorCode());
2108
2109 m_dataLoadToken.clear();
2110
2111 cancelPolicyCheckIfNeeded();
2112
2113 if (mainResourceLoader())
2114 mainResourceLoader()->cancel(error);
2115
2116 clearMainResource();
2117
2118 mainReceivedError(error);
2119}

2170void DocumentLoader::startIconLoading()
2171{
2172 static uint64_t nextIconCallbackID = 1;
2173
2174 auto* document = this->document();
2175 if (!document)
2176 return;
2177
2178 if (!m_frame->isMainFrame())
2179 return;
2180
2181 if (document->url().isEmpty() || document->url().protocolIsAbout())
2182 return;
2183
2184 m_linkIcons = LinkIconCollector { *document }.iconsOfTypes({ LinkIconType::Favicon, LinkIconType::TouchIcon, LinkIconType::TouchPrecomposedIcon });
2185
2186 auto findResult = m_linkIcons.findMatching([](auto& icon) { return icon.type == LinkIconType::Favicon; });
2187 if (findResult == notFound)
2188 m_linkIcons.append({ document->completeURL("/favicon.ico"_s), LinkIconType::Favicon, String(), std::nullopt, { } });
2189
2190 if (!m_linkIcons.size())
2191 return;
2192
2193 Vector<std::pair<WebCore::LinkIcon&, uint64_t>> iconDecisions;
2194 iconDecisions.reserveInitialCapacity(m_linkIcons.size());
2195 for (auto& icon : m_linkIcons) {
2196 auto result = m_iconsPendingLoadDecision.add(nextIconCallbackID++, icon);
2197 iconDecisions.uncheckedAppend({ icon, result.iterator->key });
2198 }
2199
2200 m_frame->loader().client().getLoadDecisionForIcons(iconDecisions);
2201}
2202
2203void DocumentLoader::didGetLoadDecisionForIcon(bool decision, uint64_t loadIdentifier, CompletionHandler<void(SharedBuffer*)>&& completionHandler)
2204{
2205 auto icon = m_iconsPendingLoadDecision.take(loadIdentifier);
2206
2207 // If the decision was not to load or this DocumentLoader is already detached, there is no load to perform.
2208 if (!decision || !m_frame)
2209 return completionHandler(nullptr);
2210
2211 // If the LinkIcon we just took is empty, then the DocumentLoader had all of its loaders stopped
2212 // while this icon load decision was pending.
2213 // In this case we need to notify the client that the icon finished loading with empty data.
2214 if (icon.url.isEmpty())
2215 return completionHandler(nullptr);
2216
2217 auto iconLoader = makeUnique<IconLoader>(*this, icon.url);
2218 auto* rawIconLoader = iconLoader.get();
2219 m_iconLoaders.add(WTFMove(iconLoader), WTFMove(completionHandler));
2220
2221 rawIconLoader->startLoading();
2222}
2223
2224void DocumentLoader::finishedLoadingIcon(IconLoader& loader, SharedBuffer* buffer)
2225{
2226 // If the DocumentLoader has detached from its frame, all icon loads should have already been cancelled.
2227 ASSERT(m_frame);
2228
2229 if (auto callback = m_iconLoaders.take(&loader))
2230 callback(buffer);
2231}

2245ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy DocumentLoader::shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToPropagate() const
2246{

2336ResourceError DocumentLoader::contentFilterDidBlock(ContentFilterUnblockHandler unblockHandler, WTF::String&& unblockRequestDeniedScript)
2337{
2338 unblockHandler.setUnreachableURL(documentURL());
2339 if (!unblockRequestDeniedScript.isEmpty() && frame()) {
2340 unblockHandler.wrapWithDecisionHandler([scriptController = makeWeakPtr(frame()->script()), script = unblockRequestDeniedScript.isolatedCopy()](bool unblocked) {
2341 if (!unblocked && scriptController)
2342 scriptController->executeScriptIgnoringException(script);
2343 });
2344 }
2345 frameLoader()->client().contentFilterDidBlockLoad(WTFMove(unblockHandler));
2346 return frameLoader()->blockedByContentFilterError(request());
2347}
